        <heading>Section </heading>
        <content>
          <p>CHAPTER 7.  OF THE OBLIGATIONS OF THE SELLER
Art. 2474.  Construction of ambiguities respecting obligations of seller
The seller must clearly express the extent of his obligations arising from the contract, and any obscurity or ambiguity in that expression must be interpreted against the seller.</p>
        </content>
